    Page: 41
    Verse: 2
Tags:
  - Cause
---
Never goes a sin without its due return; and deeds of noble goodness, or
dire sin, bear their just fruit, here, in this very life. Never is there
escape from consequence, because the Great Judge dwells within each heart.
